-- Taiwanese Stocks: Chunghwa Telecom, Hon Hai, Want Want China
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-07-17T05:40:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/taiwanese-stocks-chunghwa-telecom-hon-hai-want-want-china.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The  Taiex Index (TWSE)  rose 0.5 percent to 7,127, its first gain
in four days.  Chunghwa Telecom Co. (2412)  (2412 TT), a telecommunication
operator, rose 1.4 percent to NT$89.5. The company signed an
agreement with Arkadin for a partnership yesterday.  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317 TT), the maker of
Apple Inc. iPads, added 1.1 percent to NT$88.5. The company’s
earnings may recover in the second half of the year and 2013,
Deutsche Bank AG said in a note.  Want Want China Holdings Ltd. (151)  (9151 TT),  China ’s largest
maker of rice cake, fell 1.2 percent to NT$36.55, the lowest in
almost two weeks. A large warehouse owned by Want Want in
China’s east city of Changsha was destroyed by a fire yesterday
with a property loss of over 100 million  yuan  ($15.7 million),
the Hong Kong Economic Journal reported. Wang Yi, a company
representative, declined to comment immediately.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
